public class ModelLoadWorker
extends javax.swing.SwingWorker<java.util.List<MetaClass>,java.lang.Void>

ModelLoadWorker class for doing the main tasks separated from the EDT. Worker threads perform long running calculations or input/output (I/O) bound tasks. Worker threads are used for tasks such as communicating with databases, accessing web resources, and reading or writing large files.

The framework automatically runs it as a background thread. When the task completes successfully, it updates the UI with a dialog.

This worker thread loads Ecore meta models into the system.

protected java.util.List<MetaClass> doInBackground()

method does the main task loading the Ecore file and building the data structure out of it. The time for that task depends on the size of the Ecore model. The more classes and attributes are there, the more time is needed to parse it and build up the data structure.
